Mirror contract changes

Objective

Remove honesty caveats where real 3D structure now exists.

Current state

Some bindings likely describe 3D as partial, faceted, or degenerate.

Required update

Revise example contracts so they distinguish:

* 2D verified mode
* 3D true-front mode

Example direction

two_peak_example.json

Keep as honest 2D:

{
  "geometryMode": "2D_VERIFIED",
  "phiFamily": ["Facet-A"]
}

three_peak_example.json

Upgrade to honest non-degenerate 3D:

{
  "geometryMode": "3D_TRUE_FRONT",
  "phiFamily": ["Facet-A", "Facet-C"],
  "frontRank": 2,
  "degenerate": false
}

Do not overclaim polyhedral fullness unless the reachable structure justifies it. “True front” is safer than “full volume” unless verified.

