Kernel changes

Objective

Make runtime geometry classification reflect the corrected front.

File

* oracleKernelCore.ts

Required additions or updates

New or updated fields

* geometryMode
* frontRank
* degenerate
* activeFacetSet
* envelopeClass

Existing fields that must remain coherent

* inPhiAttractor
* attractorId
* lawCompliance

Runtime rule

The kernel must compute envelope membership against the corrected geometry, not a cosmetically altered projection.

Example response shape

type EnvelopeEvaluation = {
  insideEnvelope: boolean;
  envelopeClass: "TWO_PEAK" | "THREE_PEAK_TRUE_FRONT";
  geometryMode: "2D_VERIFIED" | "3D_TRUE_FRONT";
  frontRank: 1 | 2;
  degenerate: boolean;
  activeFacetSet: string[];
  inPhiAttractor: boolean;
  attractorId: "G_phi" | null;
  lawCompliance: {
    phiA: boolean;
  };
};

