Regression requirements

1. No break to φ-A law path

* existing attractor classifications remain stable where geometry change should not affect them
* inPhiAttractor semantics must not drift

2. 2D mode unchanged

* two_peak_example.json must evaluate identically to v0.3.1 unless fields were renamed for clarity
* no regressions in verified 2D workflows

3. 3D mode meaningfully changes

At least one realistic input class must now yield a different result than the degenerate implementation.

This is essential. If no outcome changes, the geometry fix is not operationally meaningful.

4. P2 non-redundancy

There must exist reachable states where the middle/front point participates materially in classification.

5. Honest metadata

No mirror or UI text should retain “advanced 3D” language if it still implies optional cosmetics. It must now indicate real geometry.

